<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1813948-what-was-the-point-of-the-extracts-from">What was the point of the extracts from the Drought Act 1976 at the beginning of each section of this book? I thought it might allude to something; if it did, I didn&#39;t get it.</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1813948'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F16077150-instructions-for-a-heatwave">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1813948-what-was-the-point-of-the-extracts-from">one year ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1813948-what-was-the-point-of-the-extracts-from">Add your answer</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/1598886-ian-mapp"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1291393306i/1598886._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/1598886-ian-mapp">Ian Mapp</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">There&apos;s an interview with the author at the back of my paperback. She was saying it was written during the icelandic volcano crisis and she had observ<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">There's an interview with the author at the back of my paperback. She was saying it was written during the icelandic volcano crisis and she had observed how a natural disaster had caused people to add oddly, as though they felt so obsolete and small when faced with the something out of their control.<br /><br />The Hot Summer of 76 was a similar crisis and sticks in the memory of those who lived through it. The Drought act extracts were highlighting just how serious a time it was - food shortages expected, water rationing etc. It's a backdrop as to why the Riodarden's exploded as a family.<br /><a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

