<div id="review_2739595100" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2739595100" />
    <a title="Lotte" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/25309949-lotte"><img alt="Lotte" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1408555448p2/25309949.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2739595100?book_show_action=true">Jul 02, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lotte" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lotte" href="/user/show/25309949-lotte">Lotte</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780755358793" href="/book/show/18399837-instructions-for-a-heatwave">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/25309949-lotte?shelf=a-fiction">a-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/25309949-lotte?shelf=reviewed">reviewed</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/25309949-lotte?shelf=t-multigenerational">t-multigenerational</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/25309949-lotte?shelf=ge-historical-fiction">ge-historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/25309949-lotte?shelf=recent-favourites">recent-favourites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/25309949-lotte?shelf=t-summer-reads">t-summer-reads</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/25309949-lotte?shelf=2019-read">2019-read</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2739595100" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer447997098829278521">I didn&apos;t expect to love this as much as I did. This book is a quiet, character-driven portrait of a family living in 1970s London and an absolute masterclass in writing. Maggie O&apos;Farrell dwells on the details of the sometimes seemingly mundane or everyday aspects of life but in a way that always tells you something significant about the characters, their relationships or the setting. She manages to capture the atmosphere of a place just as well as display the inner workings of someone&apos;s mind and</span>
  <span id="freeText447997098829278521" style="display:none">I didn't expect to love this as much as I did. This book is a quiet, character-driven portrait of a family living in 1970s London and an absolute masterclass in writing. Maggie O'Farrell dwells on the details of the sometimes seemingly mundane or everyday aspects of life but in a way that always tells you something significant about the characters, their relationships or the setting. She manages to capture the atmosphere of a place just as well as display the inner workings of someone's mind and all the juxtaposing and conflicting feelings that characterise relationships between siblings. The writing and the focus on family dynamics reminded me of Celeste Ng's novels (both of which I absolutely loved) and like in Ng's books, I truly cared for the characters O'Farrell creates – even though I didn't exactly like some of them – and felt totally immersed in their world. I'd highly, highly recommend this book and cannot wait to read Maggie O'Farrell's other backlist titles!</span>
  <a data-text-id="447997098829278521" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


