<div id="review_3464527927" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3464527927" />
    <a title="Janelle" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/88713906-janelle"><img alt="Janelle" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1581393896p2/88713906.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3464527927?book_show_action=true">Jul 29, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Janelle" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Janelle" href="/user/show/88713906-janelle">Janelle</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/88713906-janelle?shelf=2020">2020</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/88713906-janelle?shelf=library">library</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3464527927" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10974628747439254855">My first Maggie O’Farrell was <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/26128897.This_Must_Be_the_Place' title='This Must Be the Place by Maggie O&apos;Farrell' rel='nofollow noopener'>This Must Be the Place</a> which I read last year and really enjoyed. I knew I should read more of her work but have only just got around to this one now. <br/>As soon as I started I was immersed in her writing and wanted to know all about this family. <br/>Set in the mid70s in England when there was a heatwave and drought with water restrictions, there’s a slowness and oppressiveness in the early part of the book so I could feel the heat as I was reading.<br/>She writes wonderfully a</span>
  <span id="freeText10974628747439254855" style="display:none">My first Maggie O’Farrell was <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/26128897.This_Must_Be_the_Place" title="This Must Be the Place by Maggie O'Farrell" rel="nofollow noopener">This Must Be the Place</a> which I read last year and really enjoyed. I knew I should read more of her work but have only just got around to this one now. <br />As soon as I started I was immersed in her writing and wanted to know all about this family. <br />Set in the mid70s in England when there was a heatwave and drought with water restrictions, there’s a slowness and oppressiveness in the early part of the book so I could feel the heat as I was reading.<br />She writes wonderfully about this Irish family with all the complications of relationships, history and secrets. It naturally dips into the past as the characters recall incidents as they affect the present. <br />The only thing annoying about it is that it ends it when she could’ve said so much more!</span>
  <a data-text-id="10974628747439254855" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
